  "texts": [
    "The black circle in (a) marks the point beyond which the Ising transition and the Z2 NM phase disappear within our numerical accuracy, while the black circle in (b) denotes the location where the first-order transition splits into two BKT transitions.",
    "The EEs are computed via isotropic CTMRG on the dual lattice with χ = 128.",
    "(c) Histograms of the effective clock angles obtained with CMC for a lattice of linear size L = 64, at Z + 6 AFM ⊕ Z2 NM (T = 0.14) and Z - 6 AFM ⊕ Z2 NM (T = 0.17) phases with J2/J1 = 0.52.",
    "(d) Histograms of the local clock angles from a single CMC snapshot, corresponding to the same parameter points as in (c).",
    "(e) Observables for J2/J1 = 0.52 as functions of T /J1, including EEs (in both original and dual lattices), and the order parameters ⟨e iθ ⟩ and κ."
